<TEXT type="str">Marty Rotella, three-time Grammy nominee and award-winning singer, songwriter and musician who frequently appears on EWTN’s “Sunday Night Prime” and “Back Stage,” will perform a special benefit concert at Loreto on the Plains, 1270 Central Ave. in Hartley, at 7 p.m. Feb. 9. 
 
Rotella captivates audiences of all ages with an evening of faith, music and joy as he shares the Love of Jesus and His Mother with his gift of song and story, telling of his life’s experiences that brought him to the Heart of Jesus. Admission is free. A free-will offering will benefit Loreto on the Plains. For more Information, contact Ed and Nan Webber at 806-361-5097. 
 
First Christian Church, 3001 Wolflin Ave., will have a “Blue Jean, Be the Message Sunday” today during its regular worship service at 10 a.m. Members are asked to wear comfortable clothes and “put the love of Jesus into action” by helping pack small kits for various groups to distribute to the homeless. The kits will include items like bottled water, healthy snacks, warm gloves and toiletries. Visitors are welcome to attend and participate. For more information, call the church at 806-355-6526. 
 
St. Luke Presbyterian Church, 3001 Bell St., will have its annual congregational meeting at noon today. Before the meeting, during the 11 a.m. worship service, the elementary Logos children will sing “I’m Gonna Sing.” The Chancel Choir will present “Song of Gathering,” led by Bob Hansen and accompanied by Mila Abbasova. Rev. Elaine Besthorn will lead the service. Members are welcome to meet in the new addition to the building for a slab signing after the congregational meeting. 
 
St. Ann’s Catholic Church of Bovina is having its annual German Sausage Dinner from 11:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. today at St. Ann’s Parish Hall on Third Street in Bovina. The menu includes homemade German sausage, creamed potatoes and gravy, green beans, homemade sauerkraut, cranberry sauce, relish plate, homemade bread, homemade desserts, tea and coffee. 
 
Donations are $12 for adults and $6 for children under six. Take-out plates are available at no additional charge. 
 
Clauddell Wright continues a series of prophetic teaching on the subject of “The Full Divine Nature of God” at 10 a.m. Saturdays at 3701 Plains Blvd. The subject of due process of law in the Spirit is taught and prophesied in depth. The meetings are open to the public and will continue on Saturday mornings until further notice. Feel free to bring your Bible and note pad. For more information, call 806-671-3311 or 806-353-0374. 
 
Rev. Addae Ama Kraba will speak on “Africans in America” in 9:30 and 11 a.m. worship services Feb. 5 at Amarillo Unitarian Universalist Fellowship, 4901 Cornell St. What began as a weeklong celebration in 1926 eventually evolved into a month of celebrating the achievements of African Americans. 
 
Want to include your event? Send your faith event information to faith@amarillo.com at least a week in advance.</TEXT> 
